      {
        "hadithnumber": 1534,
        "arabicnumber": 1534,
        "text": "Narrated Ibn 'Umar:That the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) came across 'Umar while he was on his mount, and he was swearing by his father. So the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: \"Verily Allah prohibits you from swearing by your fathers. So let the one who swears, swear by Allah, or be silent",
        "grades": [
          {
            "name": "Ahmad Muhammad Shakir",
            "grade": "Sahih"
          },
          {
            "name": "Al-Albani",
            "grade": "Sahih"
